==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subsequent
<hw>Sub"se*quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subsequens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>subsequi</ets>
to follow, succeed: cf. F. <ets>subs⟦eacute⟧quent</ets>. See
<er>Sue</er> to follow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Following in time;
coming or being after something else at any time, indefinitely; <as>as,
<ex>subsequent</ex> events; <ex>subsequent</ex> ages or years; a period
long <ex>subsequent</ex> to the foundation of Rome</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Following in order of place; succeeding; <as>as, a
<ex>subsequent</ex> clause in a treaty</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>subsequent</xex> words come on before the precedent vanish.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subsequently</ent>⟦br⟧
